TL;DR: buy their laptop if you want them on the same OS/Tools (not salient
here as we operate in Google's ecosystem primarily), or set them up with an
AWS virtual workstation (not likely to be as performant as will be reliant
on their 'net connection) for the same reason.

Otherwise it looks like it's just good practice - 2FA, password rotation,
security updates, etc. It occurs to me that we may have to provide hardware
for our first hires as they're likely to be quite junior and may not have
access to quality gear up front... and that a gesture like this might
create a strong loyalty component.

FWIW - let's talk Thursday.
